Greetings,I was in the 101st abn Jun.70 thru May 71 I have a brother-in-law Marine that did two tours 68-70.We've oftened talked of dealing with the fact that what we did and what we saw has not affected us the way it seems to have others.the fact that we were both volenters and both took it as the only adventure going on at the time might have something to do with it.But we both question ourselves from time to time..are we the ones that are sick?Jim Anglin 426 s&amp;s bn. co.B[riggers]101st ABN
